This paper deals with learning the directed structure of a Bayesian network using data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a method based on the notion of "low rankness" of conditional probability tables, which is a concept that is closely related to linear algebra and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
